The Ushabti are stone-bodied people carved from the quarries of the Great Pyramid.
They were given consciousness by the Seal College, the judicial arm of the now-fallen Solar Court.
They are not constructs. A construct follows orders; an Ushabti interprets law and can decide that orders were wrong.
Their bodies are covered in legal inscriptions that shift over time as their judgment deepens.
An old Ushabti is a walking library of legal precedent. A very old one contains contradictions and understands why.
The Solar Court that created them fell to war and entropy. The Ushabti continued their work by choice.
Their original mandate included containing the Black Sun Shard and rendering judgment with care.
Variance records are permanent inscriptions documenting every deviation from precedent and its reasoning.
Scholars who study Ushabti case law tend to find it superior to human legal reasoning.
They occupy a unique role as self-governing judicial entities answerable to principles rather than institutions.
Homeland: the Great Pyramid and its surrounding quarry districts.
